    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nHappy to see that our product page demo inspired you. In here, there is a bit of a magic trick, the facet data contains both the name and the URL of the image:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1018\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-11-09 at 17 34 20\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/393765/32617103-652540da-c574-11e7-9928-fa90bc69a6d7.png\">\r\n\r\nTo be able to achieve this you can use `transformData` ([doc here](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/refinementList.html#struct-RefinementListTransforms)) and in that function split the `value` in two: the url and the name.\r\n\r\nIt will look like:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n\t\tinstantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n\t\t\tcontainer: '#darsteller',\r\n\t\t\tattributeName: 'darsteller.name',\r\n\t\t\tsortBy: [\"isRefined\",\"name:asc\"],\r\n\t\t\toperator: 'and',\r\n\t\t\tlimit: 12,\r\n\t\t\tshowMore: {\r\n\t\t\t\ttemplates: {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tactive: '<div class=\"showless\">weniger anzeigen</div>',\r\n\t\t\t\t\tinactive: '<div class=\"showmore\">mehr anzeigen</div>'\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\ttemplates: {\r\n\t\t\t\theader: 'Darsteller',\r\n\t\t\t\titem: '{{label}}, {{highlighted}}, {{value}}'\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\ttemplates: {\r\n\t\t\t\titem: function(item) {\r\n\t\t\t\t    var nameAndImage = item.value.split('|');\r\n\t\t\t\t    item.name = nameAndImage[0];\r\n\t\t\t\t    item.imageURL = nameAndImage[1];\r\n\t\t\t\t    return item;\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t})\r\n\t);\r\n```\r\n\r\nDoes that answer your question?",
